column3: can't really be used for anything.  It is resulting in errors being produced when editing the form if one is not fully aware of the underlying UI processing mechanism.  There are other issues I see
column4: that if interested we can discuss off line."

column1: "title": "Question about state of Docker containers (Artifactory properties-builder)"

"body": "I was playing with the artifactory artifact collector docker container and I noticed that the properties-builder.sh for it produced a property file with out of date syntax. ([this](https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/blob/master/collectors/artifact/artifactory/docker/properties-builder.sh#L41-L51) and [this](https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/blob/master/collectors/artifact/artifactory/docker/properties-builder.sh#L81-L103) vs [what the docs say](https://hygieia.github.io/Hygieia/artifactory.html#sample-application-properties-file))

In looking at some of the un-merged PRs I noticed one where the api and api-audit container Dockerfiles were being re-written with mounted directory for the properties file (#2767). Is that a refactor that all the containers will eventually hit? Or does the properties-builder.sh for artifactory just need some updating?

Thanks!"

"body": "I have created a new Jira cloud trial account. In the hygieia documentation username:password(encoded in base64) is mentioned for collector authentication. I am trying to authorize Jira with collector using email:password(encoded in base64) format but it's not working.  

I searched on the internet and found that Jira has already removed username field from Jira.

https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/blog/2018/06/say-goodbye-to-usernames-in-atlassian-cloud?_ga=2.159559613.184535873.1559202112-814553513.1559113992.

I tried to hit the API using postman with email:password and also bypassing basic auth key in header. but it's not working there also.


I am not sure with the issue
column2: But I have a prod instance of Jira
column3:
Where older user can able to login using username:password but new users are getting 401.



 "

column1: "body": "@tabladrum @Sbrenthughes @nireeshT @satishc1 \r\nI was using Hygieia v3.0.1 and had issues trying to get the Bitbucket collector from pulling commit history from a private repository. I did follow all the documentation. My dashboard consisted of Monitor (green - which showed that it was able to connect to my Bitbucket instance) and repo which was failing to collect the commits. The Bitbucket log showed that the request was returning a 401. When I tried to curl the same API using my Personal Access Token
column2: I successfully got back all the commits. This could only mean that something was fiddling with my Personal Access Token that led to me getting a 401. I then stumbled upon the issue https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/pull/2919 which suggests that the Personal Access Token is getting decrypted which is wrong. I have now freshly cloned the latest Hygieia repository and when I tried to build it
column3:
